  "title": {
   "en": "Bakemono no Kimi ni Tsugu"
  },
  "altTitles": [
   {
    "ja": "バケモノのきみに告ぐ"
   }
  ],
  "description": {
   "en": "In the walled city of Baldium, certain individuals develop supernatural abilities known as Unlaw—powers born from emotional trauma and mental anguish. Norman, a young man with an impressive track record of resolving mysterious cases involving these Unlaw, should have been celebrating his successes. Instead, he finds himself trapped in a dark interrogation room, forced to recount every case he’s handled—especially those involving four extraordinary girls who became his closest allies: the Teardrop, the Witch’s Hound, the Gemstone, and the Fairy.\n\nLabeled as “Monsters” by society, these girls were feared and shunned—but to Norman, they were far more than their abilities. As he revisits their stories, he unravels the tangled web of love, trust, and sacrifice that bound their fates together.\n\nThis is a tale of confessions—to the world, to each other, and to the monsters within themselves."
  },
